
DevOps focuses on speed, automation, and collaboration.
DevSecOps adds security at every stage of the DevOps lifecycle ("Shift Left Security").

Devops tools
Version Control	Git	Source code management
Code Repository	GitHub	Store and collaborate on code
CI/CD	Jenkins	Automate build, test, and deployment
Containerization	Docker	Package applications into containers
Container Orchestration	Kubernetes	Manage containers at scale
Infrastructure as Code	Terraform	Create cloud infrastructure using code
Configuration Management	Ansible	Automate server configuration
Monitoring	Prometheus	Collect metrics and monitoring
Visualization	Grafana	Dashboards and monitoring reports
Cloud Platform	Amazon Web Services (AWS)	Cloud infrastructure and services


DevSecOps Security Tools
Security Area	Tool	Use
Code Quality & SAST	SonarQube	Find bugs, vulnerabilities, code smells
Container Scanning	Trivy	Scan Docker images for vulnerabilities
Dependency Scanning	Snyk	Detect vulnerable libraries/packages
IaC Security	Checkov	Scan Terraform and CloudFormation code
Dynamic Security Testing	OWASP ZAP	Test running web applications
Secrets Detection	Gitleaks	Detect passwords, API keys in code
Kubernetes Security	kube-bench	Check Kubernetes security best practices
Cloud Security	Prowler	AWS security assessment
